# CentrAI-Chat Project Context

## What This Is

CentrAI-Chat is an open-source centralized AI conversation platform. Two personas:

- **End User** — chats with published agents or admin-enabled LLM models. No access to agent internals or admin UI.
- **Admin / Developer** — creates agents, configures providers, manages users. Superset of end-user capabilities.

## Architecture

- **Monorepo**: Turborepo + pnpm workspaces
- **Frontend**: Next.js (App Router) in `apps/web/`
- **Backend API**: NestJS in `apps/api/`
- **Worker**: BullMQ job processor in `apps/worker/`
- **Shared packages**: `packages/ui`, `packages/sdk`, `packages/config`, `packages/types`
- **Database**: PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM
- **Queue/Cache**: Redis + BullMQ
- **Realtime**: SSE (Server-Sent Events) over HTTP streaming

## Key Domain Concepts

- **Agent**: admin-created config (system prompt + model + tools). Status: `draft` → `published` → `archived`. End users only see `published`.
- **Provider**: LLM backend (OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, Ollama). All normalized behind OpenAI-compatible adapter.
- **Conversation**: belongs to a user. Contains messages. Scoped to a workspace (single default in v1).
- **Workspace**: all entities have `workspaceId` FK. v1 uses single default workspace; multi-tenancy in v2.

## RBAC Roles (v1)

| Role | Access |
|------|--------|
| `admin` | Everything: users, providers, agents, settings, dashboard |
| `developer` | Agent CRUD + chat. No user management or system settings |
| `user` | Chat with published agents and enabled models only |

## Route Layout

- `(auth)/` — login, register, password reset (public)
- `(dashboard)/` — end-user shell: `chat/`, `settings/`
- `(admin)/` — admin shell (RBAC-gated): `agents/`, `providers/`, `users/`, `analytics/`, `audit/`, `settings/`

